HEADWORD: Elayl
<hw>E*la"yl</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ olive oil,
oil + <ets>yl</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Olefiant gas or
ethylene; -- so called by Berzelius from its forming an oil combining
with chlorine. <altsp>[Written also <asp>elayle</asp>.]</altsp> See
<er>Ethylene</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

